16/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Giorgio Bonacci, director general of the EuropeAid Co-operation Office of the European Commission, said during a visit to Sarajevo on Wednesday (15 October) that the EU is willing to extend additional support for reforms in BiH. 
Bonacci met with BiH Federation Prime Minister Ahmet Hadzipasic and Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic about efforts to join the Union. 
Bonacci acknowledged progress made, but noted several challenges remain. 
He cited the need for reforms within the Public Broadcasting System and the state administration, especially units handling negotiations with the European Commission. 
(Oslobodjenje - 16/10/03; BHTV 1, FENA - 15/10/03)
